In England, in the seven days to 06 November, there were 195,942 new confirmed cases (346.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 October, there were 233,884 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 16% (37,942 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 11 November is 8,020,241 (14,182.5 cases per 100,000 population).
